  "riddle": "1. A firm leading the charge in protecting digital realms has its base in a city known for its live music scene. What city and state form its headquarters?\n\n2. Ascend to the heights of the place where this cybersecurity titan resides, and discover how far above sea level it stands.\n\n3. Seek the knowledge repositories close to this vibrant Texas city, and uncover how many libraries dot its landscape.\n\n4. Combine your findings from clues 2 and 3 to unearth the absolute difference between the elevation you found and the count of libraries at large. \n\n5. A safeguarding art thrives in various tongues. How many languages does the article on digital defenses cover?\n\n6. Within the layers of crime-fighting, there lies an organization that safeguards national security. How many languages is this storied agency’s entry available in?\n\n7. Seek out the secretive governmental body known for its intelligence work. What is the total count of languages represented in its article?\n\n8. Explore the binary structure of the linguistic total you just uncovered. How many 1-bits can be found in the binary version of that number?\n\n9. The saga of a notorious figure who plunged into a university at a precocious age unfolds. At which age did he begin his academic journey?\n\n10. In a city famous for its modern football stadium, how many museums can you find nearby? \n\n11. Journey across the ocean to find a land of tulips and windmills; discover the number of inhabitants in this charming country.\n\n12. Extract the essence of this population figure by calculating the sum of its digits.\n\n13. To reveal a vital concept for resilience in today's world, compute the digital root of the total gathered from clues 3, 5, 9, and 10 by combining their values as follows: digital_root(20 + 76 + 14 + 20). This final result shall be a single digit.",
